Two people were left seriously injured while twelve others sustained minor injuries following a collison on the M4 North in Kwa-Zulu Natal.The exact details of the cause of the crash are unclear but will form part of a police investigation.According to Arrive Alive &#8220;paramedics and the fire department arrived at the scene and found that the twisted frame of the taxi had come to rest on its side in the bush with one person still trapped in the wreckage&#8221;.Fire fighters had to use the Jaws of Life to free the injured patients who were later treated and sent to different hospitals after they were stabilised.-TNA Reporter